{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17649961","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17649961"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T21:08:26+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T21:08:26+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18385"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18385","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18385"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.12,0.04,0.2,0.4,0.24]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11103"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74435"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11103","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11103"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18385"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"59926"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4931"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"11383"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"25744"},{"type":"contributions","id":"25745"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74435","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/74435"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 45-year-old man presents to the Emergency Department after a fall from a ladder. He reports severe pain in his right wrist and is unable to move it. He has no significant medical history and does not take any regular medications. On examination, he appears well. His pulse rate is 78/min, blood pressure 130/85 mmHg, respiratory rate 16/min, SpO2 99% on room air, and temperature 36.7\u00b0C. There is swelling and tenderness over the right wrist, with limited range of motion. An X-ray reveals an intra-articular fracture of the distal radius.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is a potential long-term complication if this intra-articular fracture is left untreated?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Chronic instability","Persistent pain","Post-traumatic arthritis","Functional impairment","Deformity"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EIntra-articular fractures involve the joint surface and, if left untreated, can lead to improper healing and alignment. This can result in \u003Cstrong\u003Epost-traumatic arthritis\u003C/strong\u003E, a condition where the joint becomes arthritic due to the uneven distribution of forces across the joint surface, leading to cartilage wear and tear.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EChronic instability\u003C/strong\u003E can occur if the fracture affects the stabilising structures of the joint, but it is not the most common long-term complication of untreated intra-articular fractures.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPersistent pain\u003C/strong\u003E is a common symptom associated with malunion or non-union of fractures, but it is often a result of the underlying arthritis or instability rather than a direct complication.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFunctional impairment\u003C/strong\u003E can result from untreated fractures due to pain, instability, or deformity, but it is a broader term that encompasses several potential outcomes.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDeformity\u003C/strong\u003E can occur if the fracture heals improperly, but it is more commonly associated with extra-articular fractures. Intra-articular fractures primarily lead to joint-related complications like arthritis.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Untreated intra-articular fractures can lead to post-traumatic arthritis due to improper joint alignment and cartilage damage.","Malunion of fractures can result in chronic pain and functional impairment.","Early and appropriate management of intra-articular fractures is crucial to prevent long-term complications."],"references":["Patton, K. T., \u0026 Thibodeau, G. A. (2018). Anthony\u0027s Textbook of Anatomy \u0026 Physiology-E-Book: Anthony\u0027s Textbook of Anatomy \u0026 Physiology-E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Sud, A., \u0026 Ranjan, R. (2021). Textbook of Orthopaedics, 2e-E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Dandy, D. J., \u0026 Edwards, D. J. (2009). Essential Orthopaedics and Trauma E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","MacGregor R, Byerly DW. Anatomy, Bony Pelvis and Lower Limb: Foot Bones. 2023 May 23. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 32491379","Ombregt, L. (2013). A System of Orthopaedic Medicine-E-Book: A System of Orthopaedic Medicine-E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"59926"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18385"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"59926","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/59926"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-25T05:22:00+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-25T05:23:27+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11103"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74435"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":n